-------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Maladwen looked over at his map of Norrath hanging on the wall and yelled, &quot;I HATE that woman!&quot; He then packed all his necessary gear together that he brings on all of his travels...it was time. He ordered his colonel to come into his office with his warm clothes. &quot;To, Halas sir?&quot; the colonel asked. Maladwen grabbed the warm clothes, mainly skins of all sorts that he'd patched together after 20 years of various huntings. &quot;No, I'm going to Velious, I got tipped off the Winnower may be down there,&quot; Maladwen was still packing his items. &quot;I wonder how much she'd be worth...&quot; <br>
<br>
The colonel raised a brow at him. Maladwen simply grabbed all he could from the man, and threw it into his bags and ran out the door. This was going to be a fun trip if he ever saw one. <br>
<br>
--------------------------------------------- <br>
<br>
In Nro... <br>
<br>
Maladwen ran across the desert, the Dervish Cutthroats almost attacked him, before they recognized who it was. Then he heard the gnome welcoming people onto the raft. &quot;WAIT!&quot; he yelled. The raft was just leaving as Maladwen jumped onto it. <br>
<br>
It nearly threw the giant barbarian off, and he scowled at him. Maladwen tipped his crested helm at him, and waited until they reached the island. The waves beat up against the raft, it was very clumsy. <br>
<br>
Finally they came up to a sandy island, and Maladwen thought it would probably be a good idea to cross it. He found a dock at the other end, and so he sat there, and waited. Just like for most boats, he waited, and waited, and waited...and waited and waited. <br>
<br>
Finally, after a few hours, it came. It was a very loud clanging boat, and he jumped onto it. Thankfully, he packed his own wine, as the gnomes somehow managed to misplace their rum (silly gnomes). He laid back, and listened to the bard next to him play his soft soothing music. <br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;If you're going to kill, do it quick, to the back, where he can't see you,&quot; Maladwen Shadowlurker when he eluded the Dwarf Bounty Hunter.<br>
